                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote scope="major" script="naskh" medium="ink">Naskh in black ink.
                        Rubrication in red ink. Copied by <persName role="scribe" key="person_f7841">Abū l-ʿAbbās
                           Ḥusayn b. Mīr ʿAlam</persName>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <lb/>
                     <label>Inscriptions</label>
                     <list>
                        <item>The <locus from="iiia" to="ixb">first to sixth left flyleaves</locus>
                           bear a variant recension of the beginning of Dihistānī’s text.</item>
                        <item>The <locus from="ia" to="ia">first right flyleaf a side (f.
                              ia)</locus> bears a note describing the re-collation and completion of
                           the defective manuscript for former owner <persName>George William
                              Hamilton</persName> in <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1863-03"
                              >March 1863</date>, presumably in <placeName>Delhi</placeName>.likely
                           in the hand of his assistant, <persName cert="high" role="wst"
                              key="person_f6587">Muhīn Dās</persName>.</item>
                        <item>
                           <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus>, adjacent to his seal impression (no.
                           1) <persName role="fmo ins aut">Muḥammad Hādī Ḥusaynī</persName> declares
                           that he purchased the manuscript in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                              notBefore="1679" notAfter="1680">1090 AH (1679–80 CE)</date>.</item>
                        <item>Folio <locus from="313b" to="313b">313b</locus> bears a description of
                           winter and and note signed by <persName role="fmo ins aut"/>Ṣādiq
                           Muḥammad Raz̤avī adjcent to the seal impression of Muḥammad ʿAlī Shāh
                           (no. 7). </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <p>Stamped binding foliate motifs. Stitched.</p>
                     <decoNote type="illustration"/>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <sealDesc>
                     <summary>Seven seal impressions of former owners, including the </summary>
                     <seal>
                        <p><label>1:</label> Folio <locus from="1a" to="1a">1a</locus> seal
                           impression of <persName>Muḥammad Hādī Ḥusaynī</persName> who bought the
                           manuscript in 1090 AH.</p>
                     </seal>
                     <seal>
                        <p> f. 1a Seal of Fāz̤il Khān Murīd dated 1114 AH; Seal of Sayyid Khān
                           Ḥusaynī dated 1218. Stamp dated 1206 AH. </p>
                     </seal>
                     <seal>
                        <p> f.1b Ex libris of Sulaymān Jāh. Ex libris of Shāh ?Ramīn </p>
                     </seal>
                     <seal>
                        <p> f.313b Ex libris of Sulaymān Jāh dated 1244 AH. Stamp of Muḥammad ʿAlī
                           dated 1234 AH </p>
                     </seal>
                  </sealDesc>
